- updated and tested on CloudStack v3.0.2, for v2.x you may need to adjust id field since new version is using uuid
- support multiple connection profile
- support with apikey or through integration api port 8096 (without key)

(commands):
console        run interactively
cmd-list       list available commands
list           list     [--cmd-opt] (vm|account|site|diskoffering|svcoffering|template|user|job|zone|network|domain)
deploy         deploy   [--cmd-opt] (vm)
destroy        destroy  [--cmd-opt] (vm)
stop           stop     [--cmd-opt] (vm)
start          start    [--cmd-opt] (vm)
usage          usage    -s 2012-05-01 -e 2012-06-01 -a 1 -type (1|2|6)
set            set      [--cmd-opt] (ldap)
remove         remove   [--cmd-opt] (ldap)
sync           sync     [--cmd-opt] (ldap)
create         create  [--cmd-opt] (account|domain)
delete         delete  [--cmd-opt] (account|domain)

available cmd-opt on list command:
--ia                                            => 'use integration api url (legacy port 8096)'
--param     [comma separated api param]         => 'parameter field'
--response  [comma separated api response]      => 'response field'
--noheader                                      => 'do not print header'
--showparams                                    => 'print supported parameter'
--showresponses                                 => 'print supported responses'
--json                                          => 'print output in json'
--site      [site profile name]                 => 'set site to be use'
--id        [id|uuid]                           => 'set id or uuid for cmd-arg'

Example:
* cloudcmd ls --site branch-profile vm (listing vm using 'branch-profile' connection)
  output:
  DISPLAYNAME              STATE       ACCOUNT        DOMAIN         NIC-IP         

  HOST1                    Stopped     heince         DEV            192.168.89.134 
  VIEWPOINT                Running     heince         DEV            192.168.89.38  
  Cougar-c01               Running     heince         DEV            192.168.89.141

* cloudcmd set --host ldap.example.com --queryfilter "(&(uid=%u))" --searchbase "ou=example,dc=com"
  --binddn "uid=user1,dc=example,dc=com"  --bindpass "demo" --ia ldap
  
* #open source LDAP example (This will get all uid user, excluding batman,robin & mrbean)
  cloudcmd sync --domainid xxx --ldaphost ldap.example.com --searchbase "dc=example,dc=com"
        --queryfilter "(uid=*)" --accmap "uid" --excludeuser "batman,robin,mrbean" --ia ldap
        
  #Microsoft AD example (This will get all user with 'user' and 'guest' prefix )
  cloudcmd sync --domainid xxx --ldaphost ldap.example.com --searchbase "dc=example,dc=com"
        --queryfilter "(|(sAMAccountName=guest*) (sAMAccountName=user*))"
        --accmap "sAMAccountName" --ia ldap
        
* cloudcmd deploy --soid xxx --tid xxx --zid xxx --name testvm1 --param networkids=xxx  vm
* cloudcmd start --id 1,3,6 vm (start vm with id 1,3 and 6)
* cloudcmd ls --param id=9c2f1c37-e317-45c0-9ec1-82d3216c0678 --response id,displayname,state vm
  (show vm with id 3, only show id,name,state field)
* cloudcmd usage -s 2012-05-01 -e 2012-06-01 -a c6e3d03f-4337-44f2-af04-b4cf28709990 -type (1|2|6)
